From joe@perches.com  Mon Jun 27 12:52:44 2011
From: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Date: Tue, 21 Dec 2010 02:16:10 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 192/271] drivers/net/*/: Use static const
Git-commit: 215faf9c5f6e319e97edea9e178123e07825c14d
Patch-mainline: v2.6.38-rc1
References: FATE#311458 FATE#311459 FATE#311460 FATE#311461 FATE#311462 bnc#698050

Upstream commit: 215faf9c5f6e319e97edea9e178123e07825c14d

Using static const generally increases object text and decreases data size.
It also generally decreases overall object size.

Signed-off-by: Joe Perches <joe@perches.com>
Acked-by: Jeff Mahoney <jeffm@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c |    6 ++++--
 1 files changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c b/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
index 03683cf..cabe155 100644
--- a/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/bnx2x/bnx2x_main.c
@@ -6211,7 +6211,7 @@ static int bnx2x_func_stop(struct bnx2x *bp)
  * @param cam_offset offset in a CAM to use
  * @param is_bcast is the set MAC a broadcast address (for E1 only)
  */
-static void bnx2x_set_mac_addr_gen(struct bnx2x *bp, int set, u8 *mac,
+static void bnx2x_set_mac_addr_gen(struct bnx2x *bp, int set, const u8 *mac,
 				   u32 cl_bit_vec, u8 cam_offset,
 				   u8 is_bcast)
 {
@@ -6403,7 +6403,9 @@ void bnx2x_set_eth_mac(struct bnx2x *bp, int set)
 
 	if (CHIP_IS_E1(bp)) {
 		/* broadcast MAC */
-		u8 bcast[ETH_ALEN] = { 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff };
+		static const u8 bcast[ETH_ALEN] = {
+			0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff, 0xff
+		};
 		bnx2x_set_mac_addr_gen(bp, set, bcast, 0, cam_offset + 1, 1);
 	}
 }
